<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/30797733-christi-poulsom"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1398278278i/30797733._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/30797733-christi-poulsom">Christi Poulsom</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">There&apos;s not that much about the animals in the zoo; a few have been killed but its not graphic. However there are a couple of quite unpleasant referen<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">There's not that much about the animals in the zoo; a few have been killed but its not graphic. However there are a couple of quite unpleasant references to animal death / cruelty outside the setting which will stay with me, and they weren't even necessary to the plot. Having said that, I would still recommend the book - when it starts about cats and later goats just skip a paragraph or two.<br /> <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
