        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2230040905" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11766944761111135456">This is a <b>suspenseful novel</b> that takes place entirely during a few hours of fear in the zoo. <br/><br/>The story is told from different points of view but the more prominent character we spend time with is the mother of a four-year old child. The novel was <b>thrilling and well-written </b>but I was disappointed by the ending.<br/><br/>Initially, I resisted reading the novel because the cover reminds me of a circus and circuses have always creeped me out. I&apos;m not referring to the <i>Cirque-Du-Soleil</i> type of circus, I&apos;m refer</span>
  <span id="freeText11766944761111135456" style="display:none">This is a <b>suspenseful novel</b> that takes place entirely during a few hours of fear in the zoo. <br /><br />The story is told from different points of view but the more prominent character we spend time with is the mother of a four-year old child. The novel was <b>thrilling and well-written </b>but I was disappointed by the ending.<br /><br />Initially, I resisted reading the novel because the cover reminds me of a circus and circuses have always creeped me out. I'm not referring to the <i>Cirque-Du-Soleil</i> type of circus, I'm referring to the ones that traveled around with animals and force them to perform. In my childhood memories those poor animals always looked sad and underfed. <br /><br />Overall, <b>I enjoyed the novel</b> but would have liked it more if the ending would have been different. Still, I recommend this book to readers of thrillers and contemporary fiction.<br /><br /><b>ABOUT THE ENDING</b><br /><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ The ending was ambiguous. Sometimes ambiguity works and makes the novel intriguing, in this case it did NOT work for me.<br />During the novel we had spent most of the time with the mother, at the end we don't know if she lives or dies. So, overall, I did not liked the ending at all.<br /> <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span></span>
