    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2072497777" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2072497777" />
    <a title="Kate Olson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13650342-kate-olson"><img alt="Kate Olson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1581440560p2/13650342.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2072497777?book_show_action=true">Sep 02, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kate Olson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kate Olson" href="/user/show/13650342-kate-olson">Kate Olson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13650342-kate-olson?shelf=adult-reads">adult-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13650342-kate-olson?shelf=book-of-the-month-club">book-of-the-month-club</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2072497777" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6254636821397730413">Sooooooo. I&apos;m rating this book as 5 stars because it provoked SUCH a visceral reaction from me, and because I read it in 2 hours and couldn&apos;t put it down even though I wanted to. BUT, I wish I hadn&apos;t read it. As a teacher who suffers severe anxiety before, during and after mandated ALICE trainings at school, and as a teacher who has MAJOR thoughts on such trainings that I can&apos;t post publicly on the interwebs, this book was a massive trigger for me. I highly expected to be triggered as a mom, but</span>
  <span id="freeText6254636821397730413" style="display:none">Sooooooo. I'm rating this book as 5 stars because it provoked SUCH a visceral reaction from me, and because I read it in 2 hours and couldn't put it down even though I wanted to. BUT, I wish I hadn't read it. As a teacher who suffers severe anxiety before, during and after mandated ALICE trainings at school, and as a teacher who has MAJOR thoughts on such trainings that I can't post publicly on the interwebs, this book was a massive trigger for me. I highly expected to be triggered as a mom, but it was the teacher part of me who almost couldn't keep reading. The teacher part of me who almost couldn't return to school after the Sandy Hook shootings. This book brought it ALL back, and I wish it hadn't. This isn't a reaction to the craft of the book, which was excellent, but just to my personal issues with the topic matter - so please know that it's a very well-written and compelling story, but not one I could read and separate myself from without having to deal with lasting anxiety. <br /><br />(Also, please respect that this is MY anxiety and I have a right to it - please don't try to convince me that it's unreasonable, as many do.)</span>
  <a data-text-id="6254636821397730413" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


