<span id="freeTextContainer398460985818660877">The only reason I didn&apos;t read this in one sitting is because I had to start it right away...on the commute.<br/><br/>An original, gripping, point-of-view thriller about a mother and her child in perilous circumstances. Gin Phillips puts you in the middle of the story.<br/><br/>Also a rare book that furnished a favourite quote: &quot;Such a system of checks and balances - parenting - of projections and guesswork and cost-benefit ratios.&quot;</span>
  <span id="freeText398460985818660877" style="display:none">The only reason I didn't read this in one sitting is because I had to start it right away...on the commute.<br /><br />An original, gripping, point-of-view thriller about a mother and her child in perilous circumstances. Gin Phillips puts you in the middle of the story.<br /><br />Also a rare book that furnished a favourite quote: "Such a system of checks and balances - parenting - of projections and guesswork and cost-benefit ratios."</span>
